channel.title: *VER 3 BETA* RS Logo Creator
channel.description:
[b][u]Ive quit coding for a bit. Source files are at the bottom if you wanna keep working on my project.[/u][/b]
----[b]Last edit , on 31th march (or something like that):----[/b] Ive added tons of new stuff, and fixed up the old version to look ALOT better. DL Link: http://bit.ly/HnFuCE (its a short link to my webhost, where i host the images) The download is at exactly 876kb. Didnt bother scanning it as i'm extremely lazy. Well, sometimes. And since I made the program, I know if it contains a virus or not, so I don't see the need of screenshooting a scan.
[B]Screenshots:[/B]
Start screen (out of date): [img]http://img844.imageshack.us/img844/9322/firstw.png[/img]
The remade V1: [img]http://img854.imageshack.us/img854/6008/oldfont.png[/img]
The official V2: [img]http://img205.imageshack.us/img205/5778/newfont.png[/img]
The beta V3: [img]http://img813.imageshack.us/img813/7356/epicsauce.png[/img]
[b][u]IMPORTANT NOTICES[/u]
*This program needs a stable internet connection to work!
*The "Useful information" group boxes and all the other group boxes contains useful information, read the information you find in them!
[b][u]Credits:[/u][/b][/b] Coding: solely me on all three versions. Images: V1 and V3 solely me, V2 95% me for combining the letters on the stones, and rest to ambientX for the images I started with.
-----------------
The program was written in Visual Basic, which you can download here: [url=http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/en-us/products/2010-editions/visual-basic-express]http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/en-us/products/2010-editions/visual-basic-express[/url]
Link to source: http://fileuploader.webs.com/Source%20files.zip
The images are not included in the source, as they are being downloaded from the internet. However, if you want the images, heres a .zip with them (including the fonts): [url=http://fileuploader.webs.com/All%20the%20pictures.zip]http://fileuploader.webs.com/All%20the%20pictures.zip[/url]
The source is licensed under this license: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/
The files are uploaded at my old webhost 'cause my new one screwed up. They are 100% safe. Last but not least, you have to read the readme.txt to understand what you're doing. Sorry for the messy codes!
